Bring the @water{300%ml}(for the rice) to the boil in a large #saucepan{} over high heat. When boiling, stir in the @basmati rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a lid on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} (still with the lid on) - the rice will continue to cook in its own steam.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} then discard the core and seeds. Chop into thin strips. Trim the top and bottom from the @carrot{1}, cut in half lengthways then thinly slice widthways. Repeat with the @courgette{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Slice the @British turkey steaks{2} widthways into thin strips and pop into a #mixing bowl{}. Season with the @Chinese five spice{1%tsp} and a pinch of @salt{}. Toss well to coat in the spice and seasoning.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat!

Heat a #frying pan{} or #wok{} over medium-high heat and add the @desiccated coconut{25%g}. Toast until golden, stirring frequently, ~{2-3%minutes} (watch carefully as it can burn easily!). Transfer to a #small bowl{} and return the frying pan to high heat. Add a splash of @oil{} and when hot add the pepper, carrot and courgette. Stir-fry until starting to soften, ~{4-5%minutes}. Transfer to a bowl and set aside for later.

Leave the pan on high heat and add another drizzle of oil. Add the turkey and stir-fry until golden on all sides, ~{2-3%minutes}. Lower the heat to medium and add the garlic. Cook, stirring for ~{30%seconds} then add the @soy sauce{25%ml}, @mango chutney{40%g} and @water{2%tbsp}. Keep cooking until the turkey is no longer pink in the middle and sauce is rich and bubbling, another ~{2-3%minutes}.

Return the cooked veggies to the pan and heat until piping hot, ~{1%minute}. Fluff the rice up with a #fork{} and stir through half the toasted coconut. Share between your plates and top with the turkey stir-fry. Finish with a sprinkling of the desiccated coconut. Enjoy!